{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 325°F. Roast hazelnuts on a baking sheet for 10 minutes, allow to cool a little.","Place sugar and vanilla sugar into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>20 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add reserved roasted hazelnuts and cocoa powder and grind <nobr>20 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add milk and heat <nobr>4 min\/212°F\/speed 4<\/nobr>, then blend <nobr>2 min\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add milk chocolate and peanut oil and melt <nobr>3 min\/120°F\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Transfer into a sterilized jar and close airtight. Allow to cool, then serve or store in the refrigerator."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 oz hazelnuts","2 oz sugar","1 tsp homemade vanilla sugar","½ - 1 oz cocoa powder","3 ½ oz whole milk","6 oz milk chocolate, in pieces","2 oz peanut oil              (optional)"]}],"id":"r91294","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-rQnkTgrHkOc\/XZWZ3PAwHjI\/AAAAAAAAeSc\/mOk3yaXeZTEoQwaK2HC6jGPD6Y9vDbnfgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_mM4MHm1y8PfCQKon.png","title":"Chocolate Hazelnut Spread","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"33 g","fat":"154 g","uom":"per 1 jar","carbohydrates":"166 g","calories":"9180 kJ \/ 2193 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking sheet, sterilized jars, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To ensure preservation, clean jars thoroughly in hot soapy water. Rinse by pouring boiling water over them. Prepare for filling by placing clean jars in a baking pan and heat in oven (212°F) until required. Pour into jars while jars are still warm and proceed as directed by the recipe","Replace vanilla sugar with ½ tsp natural vanilla extract, adding it in with milk chocolate and peanut oil.","Replace part of the milk chocolate with dark chocolate, as desired.<br>The peanut oil can be omitted for a more intensely flavored spread, however the texture will not be as velvety smooth."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","45m","1 jar"]}